[2] Cholera - South Sudan
Date: Tue 14 Feb 2017
Source: AllAfrica, CAJ News report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201702140366.html


A shortage of boats, which is a prime transport source in the region, and fuel scarcity are worsening the deadly cholera outbreak that has claimed 14 lives in crisis-torn South Sudan. The disease has spread dramatically in the Eastern Lakes state.

Health minister, Achol Marial, conceded government faced numerous challenges in addressing the outbreak, citing the presence of 1 motorboat, which is unable to cover all 28 highlands. "Lack of fuel is also affecting the motorboat operation," added Marial.

Disease outbreaks in the world's newest country have coincided with a civil war that has paralyzed the country since independence in 2011. The cholera outbreak in 2016 caused more cases and spread to more locations than in 2015.

[Byline: Jaji Bashir]

